12/06/2024,745.4151(c)(5)(B) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,12/13/2024,12/13/2024,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"Drug testing kit was expired, and drug kit manual does not have proven rates that false positive results are below 2 percent, and false negative results are below 8 percent as required by policy.","On 12/12/24, the operation submitted their compliance plan by email: 

Drug Testing-The agency is aware of the Texas Administrative Code for drug testing. There are two companies that the agency has contacted to confirm the false positive and false negative percentage the TAC states. Correspondence between the agency and the companies is attached, along with one of the drug testing inserts. Moving forward, the agency will ensure that there is proper documentation stored in an employee's personal file that is not accessible by other staff. Documentation will also provide proof of the results that were documented.  This will be done by taking a picture of the results along with providing identifying information of the employee to ensure accuracy. The agency will also require the Residential Program Director to ensure that all results are properly filed in each employee's file. "
