04/06/2021,748.4207(b)(2) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,04/20/2021,05/12/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Low,Yes,"It was identified that the operation failed to submit a new variance request for this standard. The variance expired on 2/12/2021, however, the children associated with the variance remained placed at the operation until 3/29/2021. The operation did not submit a new variance request which would allow the children to continue to remain placed at the operation after the expiration date.","On 05/12/2021, the operation's Director emailed me explaining that there was a mix up when submitting the variance. They submitted a duplicate request for the wrong children, and this was not discovered in time. Documents for variance requests were provided, and this checks out. The Director went on to say, ""In the future to ensure this does not happen again, I will check variances daily for status and make sure that the correct names are written on the variance request."""
